NNAAMMEE
       llbb - Create LoopBack examples, apps, and workspaces

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       slc lb <command> <arg> [flags]

CCOOMMMMAANNDDSS
       Supported llbb commands are:

       wwoorrkkssppaaccee [[nnaammee]]
              Initialize a workspace as a new empty directory with an optional
              _n_a_m_e. The default _n_a_m_e is "loopback-workspace".



             $ slc lb workspace my-loopback-workspace




       aappii <<nnaammee>>
       Create a LoopBack application in a new  directory  within  a  workspace
       using the given _n_a_m_e. The _n_a_m_e arg is required.



             $ cd my-loopback-workspace
             $ slc lb api my-app
             $ slc app # to run the app




       mmooddeell <<nnaammee>>
       Create  a model in an existing LoopBack application. If you provide the
       --ii or ----iinntteerraaccttiivvee flags, you will be prompted through a model config-
       uration.



             $ cd my-app
             $ slc lb model -i




       aappii--eexxaammppllee [[nnaammee]]
       Create a new LoopBack application from the sample template, in a direc-
       tory with the given name (defaults to ssllss--ssaammppllee--aapppp).



             $ slc lb api-example
             $ cd sls-sample-app
             $ slc app # to run the app




OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh, ----hheellpp
              Display this help text.

       --ii, ----iinntteerraaccttiivvee
              Run an interactive model creation. Only supported with the model
              command.

       ----ddaattaa--ssoouurrccee <<nnaammee>>
              Supply  a  custom data source when creating a model. Defaults to
              "db".

       ----aapppp <<nnaammee>>
              Specify a specific app name to attach the model to. Defaults  to
              "app".




